Senior Sales Engineer / Assistant Manager – Service (SALES-Flow/201401/01/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00006269
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Jan 6 2014
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Achieve Flow Business Unit booking goals for Lifecycle Services, as well as wireless-specific order target for the Chemical and Petrochemical cluster accounts in Singapore.
Collaborate with Flow Industry Solutions Group to drive technology adoption in the respective Accounts.
Generate additional business opportunities with effective utilization of flow service center/calibration lab.
Develop and execute Lifecycle Service account plan for installed bases.
Provide accurate and punctual forecasting reports (POR) on a monthly basis to support achieving business goals.
Develop strong relationship with power sponsors to build strong advocates in the customer’s organization and to help create a differentiated vision.
Develop a keen understanding of strategic imperatives and pains impacting the site and formulate targeted solutions around customer pains; develop site account plan for key Chemical and Petrochemical accounts.
Requirements:
Degree/Diploma in Engineering with minimum 2 years’ sales experience in the Process industry preferred.
Knowledge in Flow products preferred.
Strong analytical, problem solving and decision making skills.
Customer orientated with good interpersonal and communication skills.
Own a car.